SECTION 1.1:
Guide: Creating a GitHub Account (Maxpri Engineers)
1. Go to GitHub
Open a browser and navigate to:
https://github.com

2. Start the Sign‑Up Process
Click Sign Up in the top-right corner.

3. Enter Your Email
Use your Maxpri email if possible.
If you must use a personal email, you can add your Maxpri email later.

4. Create a Password
Choose a strong password that meets GitHub’s requirements.

5. Choose a Username
Maxpri recommends a consistent naming format:
Include your name in the real name, your display name is your choice

6. Complete Verification
GitHub will ask you to solve a simple verification challenge.

7. Select the Free Plan
The Free plan is sufficient. Organization-level features are handled by Maxpri.

8. Confirm Your Email
GitHub will send a verification link.
Open the email and confirm your account.
